WEBB-CRAWFORD CO. v. PALMER CLOTHING CO. et al. In re E. W. ADAMS & CO. et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. October 14, 1922.) No. 3941. S. C. Upson, of Athens, Ga. (Horace Holden and Frank Holden, both of Athens, Ga., on the brief), for petitioner. F. H. Colley and R. C. Norman, both of Washington, Ga., for respondents.

Before WALKER, BRYAN, and KING, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

For reasons stated in the opinion of the District Judge (In re E. W. Adams & Co., 283 Fed. 431), the petition to superintend and revise is denied.
